At the Land Fund in Plzen, police made arrests during a public competition
In the Land Fund building in Plzen, the anti-corruption police have made arrests in recent days.
The detectives handed the handcuffs to the local entrepreneur and real estate trader Lubos.
The latter had attempted to precisely manipulate a public tender for the settlement of a request for restitution in such a way that the proposed land would be obtained by a particular candidate.
He was to pay Lubos G. half a million crowns.
"At the moment I can only confirm that the police are prosecuting a person for insider criminality as part of a public tender and competition," the head of the Plzen Prosecutor's Office, Antonie Zelena, told the Pravo newspaper, knowing that it is forbidden to provide more explanations as the investigation is ongoing.
Police released the 46-year-old entrepreneur after 24 hours.
To find out how he could influence a public competition, one can only speculate on the basis of so little official information.
On a question from Pravo, the spokeswoman of the Lubomira Cerna Lands Fund said that the police had actually carried out an arrest in Plzen at a separate workplace during the public competition.
“It was a customer and in no case an employee,” she said.
The public competition according to Cerna has the real name "Call to propose rights for the transfer of land according to the Land Act" and is set up when several beneficiary candidates manifest themselves.
"These individuals propose, in the context of the appeal, a higher value of their rights to resitutions that must be settled before the value of the land is announced."
"According to the proposed rights, a ranking of the buyers is set up and the Land Fund then transfers the land to the person who proposed the highest rights," said the Fund's spokesman.
Lubos G. had, it is clear, the information concerning the persons who had registered for the appeal and as he himself is also a beneficiary because, having purchased a large number of restitution rights, he had proposed to the candidates on the field not to participate in the competition.
