A dirty vote
No one expected a perfect general election in Haiti on November 28.
But it was far worse than the outsiders who wanted to help the distressed country and plunged into fear.
There were ballot boxes and a new ballot, ballot papers scattered in the gutters, looted polling stations and intimidation.
