It is unclear whether Ms. Fernández wants to stay in politics beyond the end of her term, now that her husband is no longer at her side.
If it does, it needs to win the support of the middle class, among which Kirchnerism is highly advocated.
When the Argentines have returned from their summer vacation in March, the wave of sympathy for her will have rebounded.
If she wants to win another election, she will have to decide whether or not to repudiate, quietly, many of her husband's policies.
