After 18 months of turbulence and uncertainty, MGM finally got the green light to start all over again.
A federal bankruptcy judge in New York on Thursday officially praised the creditors’ “pre-packaged” plan that roughly $5 billion of debt would be erased; paving the way for the 86-year-old entertainment company to focus its efforts on producing and distributing movies and television shows.
