Over the course of a year, the unemployment rate rose by 0.1 points.
More broadly, 3.4 million people in metropolitan France were not working in the third quarter but wanted to work, whether or not they were available within two weeks to work and whether or not they were looking for a job.
The situation of young people in the labour market has deteriorated further, with a further increase in the unemployment rate, rising to 24.2% in the metropolis (+ 0.9 points over three months, + 0.5 points over a year) and 25% including the DOM.
