For their part, seniors experienced a slight increase in unemployment, to 6.4% in the metropolis (+0.2 points over three months as well as over a year), i.e. 482,000 people aged 50 or over, and 6.6% with the DOM.
Only the 25-49-year-olds benefited from stable unemployment in the third quarter, at 8.3% in the metropolis (-0.1 points over three months, +0.1 points over a year) and 8.8% throughout France.
